main event: Two round, glowing objects were observed in Red Durham, N. C. on 7 November 1957, with a whistling sound and creating a red glow in the sky.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 3 minutes, providing a substantial observation period.
The report includes photographs, indicating potential visual evidence of the event.
The objects were observed to be one behind the other, suggesting a specific formation or behavior.
The mention of a whistling sound adds an auditory component to the sighting.
The official conclusions varied, ranging from 'Balloon' to 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation', leaving the nature of the objects unresolved.
